The 2011 season for the {{UCI team code|VWA|2011}} professional cycling team began in January at the [[Grand Prix d'Ouverture La Marseillaise]] and ended in October at the [[Nationale Sluitingsprijs]]. It was the squad's fourth season as a professional cycling team, although its first as a [[List of UCI Professional Continental and Continental teams#UCI Professional Continental Teams|UCI Professional Continental]] team; having been part of the [[UCI Continental Circuits]] since their foundation in 2008, the team acquired a Professional Continental licence following meetings of the UCI Licence Commission in November 2010.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.uci.ch/Modules/ENews/ENewsDetails.asp?source=SiteSearch&id=NzE2MQ&MenuId=12628&CharValList=664%3B&CharTextList=&CharFromList=&CharToList=&txtSiteSearch=&SelChar214=664&LangId=1|title=Registration of UCI Professional Continental Teams for the 2011 season|date=10 December 2010|access-date=28 March 2012|work=UCI.ch|publisher=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]}}</ref>

Thus, in order to compete in any [[2011 UCI World Tour|UCI World Tour]] event, the team had to be invited in advance, by race organisers.<ref name="UCI rules">{{cite web|url=http://www.uci.ch/includes/asp/getTarget.asp?type=FILE&id=34028|title=2011 UCI Cycling Regulations|date=1 February 2011|access-date=28 March 2012|archive-date=23 June 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110623174023/http://www.uci.ch/Modules/BUILTIN/getObject.asp?MenuId=MTkzNg&ObjTypeCode=FILE&type=FILE&id=34028&LangId=1|work=UCI.ch|publisher=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]|page=2}}</ref> Although the team was not selected to ride any of the three Grand Tours held in 2011, {{UCI team code|VWA|2011|nolink=yes}} was invited to six World Tour races, all held in either the Netherlands or Belgium; [[2011 Gent–Wevelgem|Gent–Wevelgem]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uitslagen.kbwb-rlvb.com/index_bestanden/pdf/WED11GentWevelgemDeeln.pdf|format=[[Portable Document Format|PDF]]|date=25 March 2011|access-date=28 March 2012|title=Deelnemerslijst|language=Dutch|trans-title=List of participants|work=kbwb-rlvb.com|publisher=[[Royal Belgian Cycling League|Koninklijke Belgische Wielrijdersbond/Royale Ligue Velocipedique Belge]]}}{{Dead link|date=April 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> the [[2011 Tour of Flanders|Tour of Flanders]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.velonation.com/News/ID/7620/Seven-wildcards-confirmed-for-Tour-of-Flanders.aspx|title=Seven wildcards confirmed for Tour of Flanders|work=VeloNation|publisher=VeloNation LLC|date=1 March 2011|access-date=28 March 2012|first=Shane|last=Stokes}}</ref> the [[2011 Amstel Gold Race|Amstel Gold Race]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/news/amstel-gold-race-announces-first-four-wildcard-invitations|title=Amstel Gold Race announces first four wildcard invitations|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=22 February 2011|access-date=28 March 2012}}</ref> [[2011 La Flèche Wallonne|La Flèche Wallonne]],<ref name="ASO">{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/news/paris-roubaix-fleche-and-liege-teams-announced|title=Paris-Roubaix, Flèche and Liège teams announced|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=4 March 2011|access-date=28 March 2012|quote=As for Flèche Wallonne and Liège-Bastogne-Liège, scheduled on April 20 and 24, the seven wildcard entries include three French teams - Cofidis, FDJ, Saur-Sojasun - as well as Belgian teams Landbouwkrediet, TopSport Vlaanderen, Veranda’s Willems Accent and Dutch squad Skil-Shimano.}}</ref> [[2011 Liège–Bastogne–Liège|Liège–Bastogne–Liège]]<ref name="ASO"/> – all single-day races held in either March or April – and the [[2011 Eneco Tour|Eneco Tour]], a stage race held in August.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.radsport-news.com/sport/sportnews_70548.htm|title=Auch Skil-Shimano, Cofidis und Verandas Willems bei Eneco-Tour|work=Radsport News|publisher=Sport Aktiv Media GmbH|language=German|trans-title=Also, Skil-Shimano, Cofidis and Verandas Willems at Eneco Tour|date=16 July 2011|access-date=28 March 2012}}</ref>

Veranda's Willems-Accent took only five victories during the 2011 season, of which three came in summer stage races. [[Steven Caethoven]] took the final stage victory at the Delta Tour Zeeland in the Netherlands, while [[Stefan van Dijk]] and [[Jurgen Van Goolen]] won stages at the [[Route du Sud]] race, held in the south of France. The team also recorded no fewer than 28 top-ten placings in single-day races, including two victories for [[Evert Verbist]] at the [[Beverbeek Classic]] in February and [[Gregory Habeaux]] at [[Dwars door het Hageland]] in July. Although not winning any of the races, van Dijk was the team's most consistent performer, and ended the season in sixth place in the [[2010–2011 UCI Europe Tour|UCI Europe Tour]] points standings,<ref name="Van Dijk">{{cite web|url=http://www.uci.html.infostradasports.com/cache/2/TheASP.asp@PageID=19007&TaalCode=2&StyleID=0&SportID=102&CompetitionID=23877&EventID=12146&GenderID=1&ClassID=1&SeasonID=480&EventPhaseID=633509&Phase1ID=0&ContainerEventID=12146&Detail=1&PageNr0=-1&Cache=2.html|title=2010–2011 Europe Tour Ranking – Individual|work=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]|publisher=Infostrada Sports|date=16 October 2011|access-date=28 March 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131016131304/http://www.uci.html.infostradasports.com/cache/2/TheASP.asp%40PageID%3D19007%26TaalCode%3D2%26StyleID%3D0%26SportID%3D102%26CompetitionID%3D23877%26EventID%3D12146%26GenderID%3D1%26ClassID%3D1%26SeasonID%3D480%26EventPhaseID%3D633509%26Phase1ID%3D0%26ContainerEventID%3D12146%26Detail%3D1%26PageNr0%3D-1%26Cache%3D2.html|archive-date=2013-10-16|url-status=dead}}</ref> while [[Staf Scheirlinckx]] took an eighth-place finish at World Tour level, in the Tour of Flanders.

==2011 roster==
In line with the squad's promotion to the second-tier of [[Union Cycliste Internationale|UCI]]-registered racing, {{UCI team code|VWA|2011|nolink=yes}} were allowed to utilise more riders on their roster as a [[List of UCI Professional Continental and Continental teams#UCI Professional Continental Teams|UCI Professional Continental]] team. As a [[List of UCI Professional Continental and Continental teams#UCI Continental Teams|UCI Continental]] team, the team was only allowed to have a maximum of sixteen riders on their roster at any one time,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uci.ch/includes/asp/getTarget.asp?type=FILE&id=34028|title=2010 UCI Cycling Regulations|date=1 July 2010|access-date=28 March 2012|archive-date=15 October 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101015062304/http://www.uci.ch/Modules/BUILTIN/getObject.asp?MenuId=MTkzNg&ObjTypeCode=FILE&type=FILE&id=34028&LangId=1|work=UCI.ch|publisher=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]|page=159|quote=2.17.004: A continental or women's team will comprise riders who may or may not be professional, in the elite and/or under 23 men's categories for a continental team and elite women's category for a women's team. It must have between 8 and 16 riders.}}</ref> while at Professional Continental level, rosters could range from sixteen to twenty-five riders.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uci.ch/includes/asp/getTarget.asp?type=FILE&id=34028|title=2011 UCI Cycling Regulations|date=1 February 2011|access-date=28 March 2012|archive-date=23 June 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110623174023/http://www.uci.ch/Modules/BUILTIN/getObject.asp?MenuId=MTkzNg&ObjTypeCode=FILE&type=FILE&id=34028&LangId=1|work=UCI.ch|publisher=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]|page=142|quote=2.16.032: The number of riders in each professional continental team shall be no fewer than sixteen (16). The maximum number of riders who may be registered with the UCI for a given professional continental team is limited to twenty-five (25).}}</ref> Over the course of the season, the team had twenty full-time riders on their books – up from sixteen riders in 2010, with twelve riders joining the team and eight riders leaving – while {{UCI team code|SKT|2011}} rider [[Dries Hollanders]]<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.directvelo.com/actualite/12571-hollanders-officiellement-stagiaire-chez-verandas-willems.html|title=Hollanders officiellement stagiaire chez Vérandas Willems|language=French|trans-title=Hollanders officially an intern at Verandas Willems|work=DirectVelo|publisher=Association Le Peloton|date=8 June 2011|access-date=28 March 2012|first=Francis|last=Spruyt}}</ref> and [[Kevin Van Den Noortgate]], a rider from amateur team EFC-Quick Step,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.directvelo.com/actualite/13801-kevin-van-den-noortgate-stagiaire-chez-verandas-willems.html|title=Kévin Van Den Noortgate stagiaire chez Vérandas Willems|language=French|trans-title=Kevin Van Den Noortgate an intern at Verandas Willems|work=DirectVelo|publisher=Association Le Peloton|date=2 August 2011|access-date=28 March 2012|first=Francis|last=Spruyt}}</ref> joined the team in the second half of the season, on short-term contracts, serving as trainee riders or ''stagiaires''.<ref name="VWA 2011">{{cite web|url=http://62.50.72.82/ucinet/default.asp?page=UCITeamsdetail&discipline=ROA&continent=ALL&teamscategory=&teamstype=PCT&year=2011&teamnameid=2974&npage=&search=&l=ENG|title=Veranda's Willems-Accent (VWA) - BEL|access-date=28 March 2012|work=[[UCI Continental Circuits]]|publisher=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160312160555/http://62.50.72.82/ucinet/default.asp?page=UCITeamsdetail&discipline=ROA&continent=ALL&teamscategory=&teamstype=PCT&year=2011&teamnameid=2974&npage=&search=&l=ENG|archive-date=12 March 2016|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> As such, many of the riders drafted in by the squad were experienced in the higher levels of the sport, having competed at ProTour and Professional Continental level; only two of the twelve new signings were aged 23 or under.

===Riders in===
Following the discontinuation of {{UCI team code|MRM|2010}} at the end of the 2010 season, Belgian rider [[Wim De Vocht]] dropped down from the ProTour to join the team.<ref name="De Vocht">{{cite news|url=http://www.gva.be/nieuws/sport/wielrennen/aid983025/wim-de-vocht-van-milram-naar-veranda-s-willems.aspx|title=Wim De Vocht van Milram naar Veranda's Willems|language=Dutch|trans-title=Wim De Vocht from Milram to Veranda's Willems|date=20 October 2010|access-date=29 March 2012|work=[[Gazet van Antwerpen]]|publisher=Concentra Media}}</ref> Two riders also joined {{UCI team code|VWA|2011|nolink=yes}} from another ProTour team; [[Staf Scheirlinckx]],<ref name="Velochrono">{{cite news|url=http://www.velochrono.fr/actu/transferts-cyclisme-2010-2011/|title=Transferts 2010-2011|language=French|trans-title=Transfers 2010-2011|access-date=29 March 2012|work=Velochrono.fr|publisher=Velochrono}}</ref> a domestique and former top-ten finisher at [[Paris–Roubaix]] in [[2006 Paris–Roubaix|2006]], and [[Jurgen Van Goolen]] both joined from {{UCI team code|OLO|2010}}; Van Goolen had previously signed for the Pegasus Sports project, prior to folding before the 2011 season even started.<ref name="Van Goolen">{{cite news|url=http://www.velonation.com/News/ID/7208/Impey-and-Van-Goolen-find-new-teams.aspx|first=Bjorn|last=Haake|title=Impey and Van Goolen find new teams|work=VeloNation|publisher=VeloNation LLC|date=25 January 2011|access-date=29 March 2012}}</ref> [[Steven Caethoven]] and [[Arnoud Van Groen]] left their respective Professional Continental teams {{UCI team code|LAN|2010}} and {{UCI team code|VAC|2010}} to join {{UCI team code|VWA|2011|nolink=yes}},<ref name="Velochrono"/><ref name="Goris">{{cite news|url=http://www.gva.be/nieuws/sport/wielrennen/aid977045/rob-goris-en-steven-caethoven-naar-veranda-s-willems-accent.aspx|title=Rob Goris en Steven Caethoven naar Veranda's Willems-Accent|language=Dutch|trans-title=Rob Goris and Steven Caethoven to Veranda's Willems-Accent|date=29 September 2010|access-date=29 March 2012|work=[[Gazet van Antwerpen]]|publisher=Concentra Media}}</ref> Under-23 riders [[Jaco Venter]] and [[Thomas Vernaeckt]] both competed at Continental level in 2010 for {{UCI team code|MTN|2010}} and Sunweb-Revor respectively, but joined {{UCI team code|VWA|2011|nolink=yes}} in the hopes of progressing eventually to the World Tour.<ref name="Venter">{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingsa.com/Article.aspx?uid=130|title=Jaco Venter signs with Professional Continental Team Veranda Willems - Accent for 2011 season|date=4 October 2010|access-date=29 March 2012|work=cyclingsa.com|publisher=Cycling South Africa|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111112210257/http://cyclingsa.com/Article.aspx?uid=130|archive-date=12 November 2011|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref><ref name="Vernaeckt">{{cite news|url=http://www.directvelo.com/actualite/9904-vernaeckt-pro-chez-verandas-willems.html|title=Vernaeckt pro chez Vérandas Willems|language=French|date=8 December 2010|access-date=29 March 2012|work=Directvelo.com|publisher=Directvelo|first=Francis|last=Spruyt|trans-title=Vernaeckt pro at Verandas Willems}}</ref> Also joining the team were [[Jempy Drucker]], [[Rob Goris]], [[David Kemp (cyclist)|David Kemp]], [[Bram Schmitz]] and [[Evert Verbist]].<ref name="Velochrono"/><ref name="Goris"/><ref name="Kemp">{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/news/kemp-confirms-signing-with-verandas-willems|title=Kemp confirms signing with Verandas Willems|first=Susan|last=Westemeyer|date=29 December 2010|access-date=30 November 2011|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref>

===Riders out===
[[Andy Cappelle]] was the team's most notable departure for the 2011 season; after winning the [[Polynormande]] race and a stage at the [[Rhône-Alpes Isère Tour]], Cappelle left the team to join World Tour squad {{UCI team code|QST|2011}} on a twelve-month contract.<ref name="Cappelle">{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/news/lefevere-defends-2011-transfers-and-signings|title=Lefevere defends 2011 transfers and signings|date=20 September 2010|access-date=29 March 2012|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|quote=Lefevere admitted to having difficulties because his "sponsoring contract expires after next season" and he is only offering one-year contracts...Newcomers for 2011 include Dutch national road champion Niki Terpstra, Belgian Andy Cappelle, German Gerald Ciolek and Italian Francesco Chicchi.}}</ref>  [[Fabio Polazzi]], [[Robin Stenuit]] and [[Jonas Vangenechten]] all joined {{UCI team code|WBC|2011}} for the 2011 season, with [[Cédric Collaers]] (Lotto-Bodysol), [[Sven Renders]] (Team Worldofbike.gr) and [[Hendrik Van Den Bossche]] (Donckers Koffie-Jelly Belly) all acquiring contracts for the 2011 season.<ref name="Velochrono"/> Of the eight riders to leave the team prior to the 2011 season, only [[Julien Paquet]] failed to find a team.

