==One-day races==
[[File:Stefan van Dijk 3DWV2011.JPG|thumb|Despite not winning any single-day race during the season, [[Stefan van Dijk]], pictured at the [[Driedaagse van West-Vlaanderen]], finished within the top ten on twelve different occasions. Of the twelve, eight came in the second half of the year, helping him to finish sixth in the final [[2010–2011 UCI Europe Tour|UCI Europe Tour]] points standings.]]

===Spring classics===
The team had very little success in the single-day races in the early part of the year, and it was not until February before the team achieved a top ten placing in a race. At the [[Beverbeek Classic]] in Belgium, Verbist and Dries Hollanders – who would join Veranda's Willems Accent later in the year as a [[Internship|stagiaire]] – attacked off the front of the field and in the process, set up a two-man sprint for the victory in [[Hamont-Achel]]. Verbist gapped Hollanders by a second to win the race for the second time,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/14th-beverbeek-classic-1-2/results|title=Verbist victorious at Beverbeek Classic|date=26 February 2011|access-date=1 December 2011|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> after previously winning the race in 2006 with the {{UCI team code|TSV|2006}} team.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.wielerland.nl/index.php?Itemid=36&id=15221&option=com_content&task=view|language=Dutch|title=Verbist verslaat Hollanders in Beverbeek Classic|trans-title=Verbist defeats Hollanders in Beverbeek Classic|date=26 February 2011|access-date=1 December 2011|work=Wielerland.nl|publisher=Wielerland|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120423000458/http://www.wielerland.nl/index.php?Itemid=36&id=15221&option=com_content&task=view|archive-date=23 April 2012|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> In March, van Dijk took two second-place finishes – both coming in mass sprints – at [[Omloop van het Waasland]] behind {{UCI team code|LAN|2011}}'s [[Aidis Kruopis]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/omloop-van-het-waasland-1-2-1/results|title=Kruopis claims victory in Stekene|date=14 March 2011|access-date=1 December 2011|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.standaard.be/artikel/detail.aspx?artikelid=DMF20110313_103|language=Dutch|title=Litouwer Aidis Kruopis wint Omloop van Het Waasland|trans-title=Lithuanian Aidis Kruopis wins Circuit of the Waasland|date=13 March 2011|access-date=1 December 2011|work=[[De Standaard]]|publisher=[[Corelio]]}}</ref> and the [[Nokere Koerse]] behind [[Gert Steegmans]] of {{UCI team code|QST|2011}}.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/nokere-koerse-1-1/results|title=Steegmans wins Nokere-Koerse|date=16 March 2011|access-date=1 December 2011|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref>

Later in March, Van Groen finished ninth in the [[Classic Loire Atlantique]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/classic-loire-atlantique-1-1/results|first=Jean-François|last=Quénet|title=Westra wins Classic Loire Atlantique|date=19 March 2011|access-date=1 December 2011|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> and Vanlandschoot took a sixth-place finish the next day in the [[Cholet-Pays de Loire]] race.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/cholet-pays-de-loire-1-1/elite-men/results|first=Jean-François|last=Quénet|title=Voeckler victorious at Cholet-Pays De Loire with late attack|date=20 March 2011|access-date=1 December 2011|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> In April, during one of the team's wildcard entries to a [[2011 UCI World Tour|World Tour]] race, Scheirlinckx finished in eighth place in the [[2011 Tour of Flanders|Tour of Flanders]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/tour-of-flanders-upt/results|title=Nuyens makes his big break through|date=3 April 2011|work=Cycling News|first=Brecht|last=Decaluwé|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> having bridged up to the lead group prior to the final climb of the race, the cobbled Bosberg hill, {{convert|10|km|1|abbr=on}} from the finish in [[Meerbeke]]. Van Dijk finished fourth in the [[2011 Scheldeprijs|Scheldeprijs]] three days later,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/scheldeprijs-1-hc/results|title=Cavendish prevails in Scheldeprijs|date=6 April 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> having avoided a crash in the finishing straight which eliminated several riders from contention for the top placings. This result was again followed the next day by a top ten finish by Vanlandschoot, as in the [[Grand Prix Pino Cerami]], Vanlandschoot finished in ninth place.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/grand-prix-pino-cerami-1-1/results|title=Scheirlinckx slays the Dragon|date=7 April 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> May and June brought the team two more top ten finishes each month; Verbist finished tenth in the Circuit de Wallonie,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/45th-circuit-de-wallonie-1-2/results|title=Tamayo takes Circuit de Wallonie|date=8 May 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> and eighth in the Gullegem Koerse national event in Belgium,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wielerland.nl/index.php?Itemid=242&c=u&id=27117&option=com_database&sc=1|title=Uitslag: 2011 Gullegem Koerse|trans-title=Results: 2011 Gullegem Koerse|date=31 May 2011|access-date=1 December 2011|work=Wielerland.nl|publisher=Wielerland|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120423000713/http://www.wielerland.nl/index.php?Itemid=242&c=u&id=27117&option=com_database&sc=1|archive-date=23 April 2012|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> while in June, van Dijk finished fifth in the [[Tour de Rijke]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/22nd-tour-de-rijke-1-1/results|title=Bos nets sprint win in Tour de Rijke|date=5 June 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> and Van Groen finished tenth in another national event, the [[Ruddervoorde Koerse]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/ruddervoorde-koerse-2011/results|title=Bellemakers bests Ruijgh in Ruddervoorde|date=21 June 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref>

The team also sent squads to the [[Grand Prix d'Ouverture La Marseillaise]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/grand-prix-cycliste-la-marseillaise-1-1-1/results|title=Jérémy Roy wins the Grand Prix d'Ouverture La Marseillaise|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=30 January 2011|access-date=28 March 2012}}</ref> [[2011 Omloop Het Nieuwsblad|Omloop Het Nieuwsblad]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.velonation.com/News/ID/7580/Omloop-Het-Nieuwsblad-Langeveld-takes-two-man-sprint-against-Flecha.aspx|title=Langeveld takes two-man sprint against Flecha|first=Bjorn|last=Haake|date=26 February 2011|access-date=28 March 2012|work=VeloNation|publisher=VeloNation LLC}}</ref> [[2011 Kuurne–Brussels–Kuurne|Kuurne–Brussels–Kuurne]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://velonews.competitor.com/2011/02/news/road/2011-kuurne-brussels-kuurne-results_161915|title=2011 Kuurne-Brussels-Kuurne results|work=VeloNews|publisher=Competitor Group, Inc.|date=27 February 2011|access-date=28 March 2012|archive-date=28 February 2015|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150228111745/http://velonews.competitor.com/2011/02/news/road/2011-kuurne-brussels-kuurne-results_161915|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[Le Samyn]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/43rd-le-samyn-1-1/results|title=Klemme takes first win for Leopard Trek|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=2 March 2011|access-date=28 March 2012}}</ref> [[De Vlaamse Pijl]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/de-vlaamse-pijl-1-2/results|title=Amorison solos to Vlaamse Pijl victory|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=5 March 2011|access-date=28 March 2012}}</ref> the [[Handzame Classic]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/handzame-classic-1-1/results|title=Schets takes sprint in rainy Handzame Classic|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=18 March 2011|access-date=28 March 2012}}</ref> [[Dwars door Vlaanderen]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/dwars-door-vlaanderen-a-travers-la-flandre-1-1-1/results|title=Nuyens victorious at Dwars door Vlaanderen|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=23 March 2011|access-date=28 March 2012}}</ref> [[2011 E3 Prijs Vlaanderen – Harelbeke|E3 Prijs Vlaanderen – Harelbeke]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/e3-prijs-vlaanderen-harelbeke-1-hc/results|title=Cancellara cruises to victory in late solo breakaway|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=26 March 2011|access-date=28 March 2012}}</ref> [[2011 Gent–Wevelgem|Gent–Wevelgem]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/gent-wevelgem-upt/results|title=Boonen sprints to victory|date=27 March 2011|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|access-date=28 March 2012}}</ref> [[Hel van het Mergelland]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/38th-hel-van-het-mergelland-1-1/results|title=Ligthart bests Canuti for home turf win|date=2 April 2011|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|access-date=28 March 2012}}</ref> [[Brabantse Pijl (men's race)|Brabantse Pijl]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/de-brabantse-pijl-la-fleche-brabanconne-1-hc/results|title=Gilbert wins De Brabantse Pijl|date=13 April 2011|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|access-date=28 March 2012|first=Brecht|last=Decaluwé}}</ref> the [[Grand Prix de Denain]],<ref>{{cite web|format=[[Portable Document Format|PDF]]|url=http://asso.nordnet.fr/gpdenain/00_courant/resultats2011.pdf|title=Classement de l'épreuve|language=French|trans-title=Classification of the event|date=14 April 2011|work=[[Grand Prix de Denain]]|publisher=Nordnet|access-date=28 March 2012|archive-url=https://www.webcitation.org/694ZUOWIv?url=http://asso.nordnet.fr/gpdenain/00_courant/resultats2011.pdf|archive-date=11 July 2012|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> the [[Tour du Finistère]],<ref>{{cite web|format=[[Portable Document Format|PDF]]|url=http://www.tourdufinistere.fr/images/classement-tdf2011.pdf|title=Classement de l'épreuve|language=French|trans-title=Classification of the event|date=16 April 2011|work=[[Tour du Finistère]]|publisher=Comité Régional de Bretagne de Cyclisme; [[Fédération Française de Cyclisme]]|access-date=28 March 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110427224602/http://www.tourdufinistere.fr/images/classement-tdf2011.pdf|archive-date=27 April 2011|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> the [[2011 Amstel Gold Race|Amstel Gold Race]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/amstel-gold-race-upt/results|title=Gilbert repeats at Amstel Gold Race|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=17 April 2011|access-date=28 March 2012}}</ref> the [[Tro-Bro Léon]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/tro-bro-leon-1-1-2/results|title=Jerome prevails in Tro-Bro Léon|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=17 April 2011|access-date=28 March 2012|first=Jean-François|last=Quénet}}</ref> [[2011 La Flèche Wallonne|La Flèche Wallonne]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/la-fleche-wallonne-his/results|title=Gilbert takes audacious victory atop Mur de Huy|first=Brecht|last=Decaluwé|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=20 April 2011|access-date=28 March 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110425034645/http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/la-fleche-wallonne-his/results|archive-date=2011-04-25|url-status=dead}}</ref> [[2011 Liège–Bastogne–Liège|Liège–Bastogne–Liège]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/liege-bastogne-liege-2011/results|title=Gilbert the great!|first=Brecht|last=Decaluwé|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=24 April 2011|access-date=28 March 2012}}</ref> the [[Eschborn-Frankfurt City Loop]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/rund-um-den-finanzplatz-eschborn-frankfurt-1-hc-1/results|title=Degenkolb snatches win in Frankfurt|first=Susan|last=Westemeyer|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=1 May 2011|access-date=28 March 2012}}</ref> [[Halle–Ingooigem]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/halle-ingooigem-2011/results|title=Curvers nabs Halle-Ingooigem victory|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=22 June 2011|access-date=28 March 2012}}</ref> and the [[Internationale Wielertrofee Jong Maar Moedig]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/internationale-wielertrofee-jong-maar-moedig-i-w-t-2011/results|title=Scheirlinckx wins I.W.T. Jong Maar Moedig|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=29 June 2011|access-date=28 March 2012}}</ref> but placed outside of the top 10 in all of these races.

===Fall races===
The second half of the 2011 season for Veranda's Willems-Accent was more impressive than the first half of the year, taking top ten placings in 18 out of 22 single-day races held between July and October. It began with a victory, with Habeaux taking his first professional win in Dwars door het Hageland, held in [[Aarschot]], Belgium.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/dwars-door-het-hageland-2011/results|title=Habeaux takes first pro win|date=4 July 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> Verbist finished sixth in the Grand Prix José Dubois,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://users.skynet.be/fb947394/cyclisme/Classements%20et%20photos/2011/20110717ISIERES.pdf|format=[[Portable Document Format|PDF]]|title=Grand Prix José Dubois à Isières – Pros|date=17 July 2011|work=Alarrivee.be|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=[[Belgacom Skynet]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120106150330/http://users.skynet.be/fb947394/cyclisme/Classements%20et%20photos/2011/20110717ISIERES.pdf|archive-date=6 January 2012|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> before Habeaux took another top ten finish in [[Antwerpse Havenpijl]] in August.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/antwerpse-havenpijl-1-2-2/results|title=Lang sprints to win in Antwerpse Havnpijl|date=9 August 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> Later in August, van Dijk finished third in the [[Dutch Food Valley Classic]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/dutch-food-valley-classic-1-1/results|title=Bos triumphs at Dutch Food Valley Classic|date=19 August 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> Verbist finished tenth in the [[Châteauroux Classic]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/chateauroux-classic-de-lindre-trophee-fenioux-1-1-2/results|title=Ravard wins in Châteauroux|date=21 August 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> Drucker finished sixth in the [[Grote Prijs Stad Zottegem]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/gp-stad-zottegem-1-1-1/results|title=Tuft solos to victory in Belgium|date=23 August 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> with Van Goolen adding a fourth top ten within the space of a week, with third in the [[Druivenkoers Overijse]] event.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/druivenkoers-overijse-1-1-2/results|title=Leukemans best in Overijse|date=24 August 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref>

Van Dijk then reeled off a run of five consecutive races in which he finished as the team's best rider. The run began towards the end of August with a tenth-place finish in the [[Schaal Sels-Merksem]] event,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/schaal-sels-1-1-2/results|title=Kruopis sprints to victory in Schaal Sels|date=29 August 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> which was followed by a trio of fourth places in early-September at the [[Grote Prijs Jef Scherens]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/grote-prijs-jef-scherens-rondom-leuven-1-1-1/results|title=Pineau smiling again at GP Scherens|date=4 September 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> the [[Memorial Rik Van Steenbergen]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/memorial-rik-van-steenbergen-1-1-1/results|title=Van Hummel victorious at Memorial Rik Van Steenbergen|date=7 September 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> and [[Paris–Brussels]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/parijs-brusssel-paris-bruxelles-1-hc-2/results|title=Galimzyanov prevails in Paris-Bruxelles|date=10 September 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> before a third place the day after, in the [[Grand Prix de Fourmies]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/gp-de-fourmies-la-voix-du-nord-1-hc-2/results|title=Blot tops GP de Fourmies|date=11 September 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> Later in the month, van Dijk finished eighth in the [[Kampioenschap van Vlaanderen]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/kampioenschap-van-vlaanderen-1-1-2/results|title=Kittel tops Greipel in Koolskamp|date=16 September 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> and second behind {{UCI team code|QST|2011|nolink=yes}}'s [[Guillaume Van Keirsbulck]] in [[Omloop van het Houtland]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/omloop-van-het-houtland-lichtervelde-1-1-2/results|title=Van Keirsbulck fastest of breakaway in Lichtervelde|date=21 September 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> October brought the team three final top ten placings; Verbist finished eighth in the [[Tour de Vendée]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/tour-de-vendee-1-hc-1/results|title=Marcato wins from the break|date=2 October 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> Vernaeckt took his best result of the season with ninth place in [[Binche–Tournai–Binche]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/binche-tournai-binche-1-1-1/results|title=Selig sprints to victory|date=4 October 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> and van Dijk concluded his season with fifth place in the final Belgian race of the season, the [[Nationale Sluitingsprijs]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/nationale-sluitingprijs-putte-kapellen-1-1-2/results|title=Hutarovich caps off successful season with Putte-Kapellen win|date=11 October 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref>

The team also sent squads to the [[Polynormande]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/la-poly-normande-2011/results|first=Jean-François|last=Quénet|title=Delaplace comes home as a hero|date=31 July 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=28 March 2012|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> the [[Grand Prix de Wallonie]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/grand-prix-de-wallonie-2011/results|title=Gilbert triumphs in Grand Prix de Wallonie|date=14 September 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=28 March 2012|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> the [[Grand Prix d'Isbergues]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/grand-prix-disbergues-pas-de-calais-1-1-2/results|title=Jorgensen edges O'Grady to win Isbergues|date=19 September 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=28 March 2012|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> [[Paris–Bourges]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/paris-bourges-1-1-1/results|title=Hayman tops sprint for Paris-Bourges win|date=6 October 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=28 March 2012|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> and [[2011 Paris–Tours|Paris–Tours]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.letour.fr/2011/PAT/LIVE/us/100/classement/index.html|title=Standing Élite|work=[[Paris–Tours]]|publisher=[[Amaury Sport Organisation]]|date=9 October 2011|access-date=28 March 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120126104638/http://www.letour.fr/2011/PAT/LIVE/us/100/classement/index.html|archive-date=26 January 2012|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> but placed outside of the top 10 in all of these races.

==Stage races==
Compared to the team's single-day form, Veranda's Willems-Accent were not so prominent during the stage races. Schmitz took a minor classification win at the [[Étoile de Bessèges]], winning the mountains classification comfortably, scoring more than double the points of his closest rival [[Yuri Trofimov]] of {{UCI team code|KAT|2011}}.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.etoiledebesseges.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=132&Itemid=158|title=Classement des grimpeurs|date=6 February 2011|access-date=1 December 2011|work=[[Étoile de Bessèges]]|publisher=[[Fédération Française de Cyclisme]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120502001955/http://www.etoiledebesseges.com/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=132&Itemid=158|archive-date=2 May 2012|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> The team's first stage win did not come until June, when Caethoven won the final stage of the Delta Tour Zeeland into [[Terneuzen]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/4th-delta-tour-zeeland-2-1/stage-2/results|title=Caethoven wins final stage|date=12 June 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> Later in the month, the team took two more stage wins at the [[Route du Sud]], with van Dijk winning the opening stage into [[Samatan]],<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/35th-route-du-sud-la-depeche-du-midi-2-1/stage-1/results|title=Van Dijk speeds to stage win|date=16 June 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> and Van Goolen won the third stage into [[Bagnères-de-Luchon]], having soloed to victory from an earlier twelve-man breakaway, eventually winning the stage by 96 seconds.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/35th-route-du-sud-la-depeche-du-midi-2-1/stage-3/results|title=Van Goolen triumphs in Bagnères de Luchon|date=18 June 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> Van Dijk also took out the points classification for the team,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.routedusud.fr/Etape4_2011.pdf|format=[[Portable Document Format|PDF]]|title=35ème Route du Sud la Dépêche du Midi: 4ème étape Izaourt – Pau|date=19 June 2011|work=[[Route du Sud]]|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=[[Fédération Française de Cyclisme]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110708064059/http://www.routedusud.fr/Etape4_2011.pdf|archive-date=8 July 2011|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref> which was the team's final classification win of the year. Later in the season, Degand took third place in the two-day [[Paris–Corrèze]] race.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/paris-correze-2-1/stage-2/results|title=De Waele tops final stage|date=4 August 2011|work=Cycling News|access-date=1 December 2011|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref>

The team also sent squads to the [[2011 Tour du Haut Var|Tour du Haut Var]], the [[Tour of South Africa]], [[Driedaagse van West-Vlaanderen]], the [[Three Days of De Panne]], the [[Circuit de la Sarthe (cycling)|Circuit de la Sarthe]], the [[2011 Tour of Turkey|Presidential Tour of Turkey]], the [[Four Days of Dunkirk]], the [[Tour de Picardie]], the [[2011 Tour of Belgium|Tour of Belgium]], the [[2011 Tour de Luxembourg|Tour de Luxembourg]], the [[Tour de Wallonie]], the [[2011 Eneco Tour|Eneco Tour]], the [[Tour du Limousin]], and the [[Tour de Wallonie-Picarde]], but did not achieve a stage win, classification win, or podium finish in any of them.

==Grand Tours==
As the squad was a [[List of UCI Professional Continental and Continental teams#UCI Professional Continental Teams|UCI Professional Continental]] team for the first time in 2011, they were in a position to compete in one of the three [[Grand Tour (cycling)|Grand Tours]].<ref name="UCI rules"/> As such, all eighteen [[UCI ProTour#List of current UCI ProTeams|UCI ProTeams]] were invited automatically to each of the races, meaning that {{UCI team code|VWA|2011|nolink=yes}} had to receive an invitation from each respective race organiser, in order to compete. However, the squad was not selected to ride any of the three Grand Tours; for the [[2011 Giro d'Italia|Giro d'Italia]], four of the five wildcards were largely Italian teams, with the {{UCI team code|GEO|2011}} team being the only exception.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.podiumcafe.com/2011/3/7/2034536/giro-wildcards|title=Giro d'Italia Wildcards|work=Podium Cafe|publisher=[[Vox Media, Inc.]]|date=7 March 2011|access-date=28 March 2012|first=Dennis|last=Josefsson}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.gazzetta.it/Speciali/Giroditalia/it/07-03-2011/giro-ecco-magnifiche-23-80395640006.shtml|title=Giro, ecco le magnifiche 23: Al via almeno 207 corridori|language=Italian|trans-title=Giro, here is the magnificent 23: At the minimum 207 riders|work=[[La Gazzetta dello Sport]]|publisher=[[RCS MediaGroup]]|date=7 March 2011|access-date=28 March 2012}}</ref> Four wildcards were on offer for the [[2011 Tour de France|Tour de France]], and all were received by French-based teams – {{UCI team code|COF|2011}}, {{UCI team code|EUC|2011}}, {{UCI team code|FDJ|2011}} and {{UCI team code|SAU|2011}}<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/news/tour-de-france-selects-22-teams|title=Tour de France selects 22 teams|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=20 January 2011|access-date=28 March 2012}}</ref> – and at the [[2011 Vuelta a España|Vuelta a España]], home teams {{UCI team code|ACG|2011}} and {{UCI team code|GEO|2011|nolink=yes}} were invited along with {{UCI team code|COF|2011|nolink=yes}} and Dutch team {{UCI team code|SKS|2011}}.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/news/vuelta-a-espana-wildcards-announced|title=Vuelta a España wildcards announced|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=31 May 2011|access-date=28 March 2012}}</ref>

==Season victories==
At the end of the [[2010–2011 UCI Europe Tour]] season, {{UCI team code|VWA|2011|nolink=yes}} was ranked in fourteenth place in the final Europe Tour standings,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uci.html.infostradasports.com/asp/xml/index.asp?SportID=102&PhaseID=711562|title=2010–2011 Europe Tour Ranking – Team|work=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]|publisher=Infostrada Sports|date=16 October 2011|access-date=28 March 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131227010601/http://www.uci.html.infostradasports.com/asp/xml/index.asp?SportID=102&PhaseID=711562|archive-date=2013-12-27|url-status=dead}}</ref> with a total of 879 points contributed by the team's best eight riders in the concurrent individual rankings.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uci.ch/includes/asp/getTarget.asp?type=FILE&id=34028|title=2010 UCI Cycling Regulations|date=1 July 2010|access-date=28 March 2012|archive-date=15 October 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101015062304/http://www.uci.ch/Modules/BUILTIN/getObject.asp?MenuId=MTkzNg&ObjTypeCode=FILE&type=FILE&id=34028&LangId=1|work=UCI.ch|publisher=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]|page=57|quote=2.11.008: The classification of UCI continental teams and UCI continental professional teams shall be obtained by adding the points of their 8 best placed riders in the individual classification.}}</ref> Van Dijk was the team's best placed rider on the individual rankings, finishing in sixth place with 494 of the team's points; missing out on a top-five ranking by 24 points.<ref name="Van Dijk"/> Outside of the team's continental home tour, the squad was also ranked in the [[2010–2011 UCI Africa Tour]] standings; with 14 points contributed by Degand, Venter and Habeaux at the Tour of South Africa, the team ranked in sixteenth place out of 22 points-scoring teams.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uci.html.infostradasports.com/asp/xml/index.asp?SportID=102&PhaseID=709213|title=2010–2011 Africa Tour Ranking – Team|work=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]|publisher=Infostrada Sports|date=30 September 2011|access-date=28 March 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111229071211/http://www.uci.html.infostradasports.com/asp/xml/index.asp?SportID=102&PhaseID=709213|archive-date=2011-12-29|url-status=dead}}</ref> The team also scored 40 points on the [[2010–2011 UCI Asia Tour]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uci.html.infostradasports.com/asp/xml/index.asp?SportID=102&PhaseID=709219|title=2010–2011 Asia Tour Ranking – Team|work=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]|publisher=Infostrada Sports|date=30 September 2011|access-date=28 March 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131227010414/http://www.uci.html.infostradasports.com/asp/xml/index.asp?SportID=102&PhaseID=709219|archive-date=2013-12-27|url-status=dead}}</ref> but this was due to the acquisition of results as {{UCI team code|VWA|2011|nolink=yes}} did not compete in Asia as a team during the season; David Kemp joined {{UCI team code|VWA|2011|nolink=yes}} for the 2011 season, having won the Tour of Taihu in October 2010 for Fly V Australia.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/tour-of-taihu-1-2/results|title=Kemp flies to Taihu win|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=25 October 2010|access-date=28 March 2012}}</ref>

Although the team was able to compete in [[2011 UCI World Tour|UCI World Tour]] races during the season, no points were awarded to the team following a new rule introduced by the [[Union Cycliste Internationale]], clarifying that only [[UCI ProTour#List of current UCI ProTeams|UCI ProTeams]] were eligible to score World Tour points.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.irishpeloton.com/2011/08/uci-world-championships-selection-criteria/|title=UCI World Championships selection criteria|first=Cillian|last=Kelly|date=9 August 2011|work=Irish Peloton|publisher=[[WordPress]]|access-date=28 March 2012}}</ref>

