==Away from competition==

===Sponsorship===
The team attracted a co-sponsor for the 2011 season, having been known as {{UCI team code|VWA|2010|nolink=yes}} during the 2010 season. When the list of 2011 UCI Professional Continental Teams was announced in December 2010, the team name was listed as {{UCI team code|VWA|2011|nolink=yes}}.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.velonation.com/News/ID/6679/UCI-releases-list-of-Professional-Continental-teams.aspx|title=UCI releases list of Professional Continental teams|work=VeloNation|publisher=VeloNation LLC|date=10 December 2010|access-date=29 March 2012|first=Ben|last=Atkins}}</ref> This was due to the involvement of Accent Jobs for people, a Belgian recruitment company, focusing on the job market in their native country as well as the pan-European market.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://pl.accentjobs.be/index2.html|title=Welcome at Accent Jobs for People|work=pl.Accent Jobs|publisher=Accent Jobs for People|access-date=29 March 2012}}{{Dead link|date=May 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> They joined Veranda's Willems, a Belgian manufacturer of conservatories and windows, as main sponsors of the team. Other team partners included carbonated soft drinks company [[Coca-Cola]], bicycle components company [[Miche (company)|Miche]], sports equipment manufacturer [[Oakley, Inc.|Oakley]], electronic sports equipment manufacturer [[Sigma Sport]], and many more.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.accentwillems.be/partners/|title=Partners|work={{UCI team code|WGG|2012}}|publisher=Belgian Pro Cycling Team NV|access-date=29 March 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120403195009/http://www.accentwillems.be/partners/|archive-date=3 April 2012|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>

Following the 2011 season, it was announced that Accent Jobs for People would become "the full owner/sponsor of their Pro Continental cycling team", and in effect, change the order in which the names appeared in the team's documentation; becoming {{UCI team code|WGG|2012}} for 2012.<ref name="Continue">{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/news/accent-jobs-willems-verandas-to-continue-in-2012|title=Accent jobs – Willems Verandas to continue in 2012|date=27 October 2011|access-date=29 March 2012|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> The team had hoped to acquire another main sponsor in order to provide budget for any further signings that the team may have wished to have carried out, but this did not materialise; leaving the team shy of the 20 riders they wished to have.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/news/accent-jobs-verandas-willems-hopes-to-sign-more-riders-for-2012|title=Accent Jobs-Verandas Willems hopes to sign more riders for 2012|date=13 December 2011|access-date=29 March 2012|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref> As well as a change in the background running of the team, with Wim Vanhaelemeesch replacing Bill Olivier as team manager,<ref name="Continue"/> the team also introduced a new-look kit for the 2012 season. Replacing the white-and-black kit that the team had adopted since its formation, a predominately orange kit with areas of black around the shoulders was introduced ahead of their 2012 season-opening race.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/news/gallery-accent-jobs-willems-verandas-presents-its-2012-jersey|title=Accent Jobs-Willems Veranda's presents its 2012 jersey|date=9 January 2012|access-date=29 March 2012|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited}}</ref>

===Postseason===
Six riders left the team at the conclusion of the 2011 season. Failing to take a top ten finish at any race in the season, [[Dieter Cappelle]] was not retained after two seasons with the team. [[Sven Van Den Houte]], who had been with the team since 2009, left the squad to join the Colba-Superano Ham team,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.directvelo.com/actualite/16640-sven-van-den-houte-chez-colba-superano-ham.html|title=Sven Van den Houte chez Colba - Superano Ham|language=French|trans-title=Sven Van den Houte at Colba - Superano Ham|date=29 December 2011|access-date=29 March 2012|work=DirectVelo|publisher=Association Le Peloton|first=Renaud|last=Collette}}</ref> after failing to register a top-50 finish in any race he contested in 2011. The other four riders left the squad after only twelve months with the outfit; [[Jaco Venter]] left to join {{UCI team code|CCD|2012}},<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.directvelo.com/actualite/17205-le-team-differdange-a-la-recherche-d-un-second-francais.html|title=Le Team Differdange à la recherche d'un second français|language=French|trans-title=The Team Differdange in search of a second French rider|date=13 February 2012|access-date=29 March 2012|work=DirectVelo|publisher=Association Le Peloton|first=Sébastien|last=Barré}}</ref> while [[Thomas Vernaeckt]] left to join the new Belgian-Algerian squad formed for the start of the 2012 season, Geofco Ville d'Alger.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.spaziociclismo.it/?action=read&idnotizia=15549|title=GEOFCO-Ville d'Alger, arriva Vernaeckt|language=Italian|trans-title=GEOFCO-Ville d'Alger get Vernaeckt|date=9 December 2011|access-date=29 March 2012|work=Spazio Ciclismo|publisher=Tutto Mercato Web}}</ref> [[David Kemp (cyclist)|David Kemp]] failed to garner a contract for the 2012 season, while [[Bram Schmitz]] retired from competitive racing at the age of 34; he competed as a professional between 1999 and 2011, for the {{UCI team code|TVM|1999}}, Batavus-Bankgiroloterij, {{UCI team code|TMO|2004}} and {{UCI team code|RIJ|2007}} teams, as well as his season with {{UCI team code|VWA|2011|nolink=yes}}.

Four riders joined the team ahead of the 2012 season. Following his season at {{UCI team code|QST|2011}}, [[Andy Cappelle]] rejoined the team after a winless season at {{UCI team code|QST|2011|nolink=yes}},<ref name="Ista">{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/news/cappelle-and-ista-join-accent-jobs-verandas-willems|title=Cappelle and Ista join Accent Jobs-Verandas Willems|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=24 November 2011|access-date=29 March 2012}}</ref> although he did finish runner-up to {{UCI team code|EUC|2011}}'s [[Anthony Charteau]] in January's [[La Tropicale Amissa Bongo]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/races/la-tropicale-amissa-bongo-tabo-2-1-1/stage-6/results|title=Charteau wins overall in Gabon|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=30 January 2011|access-date=29 March 2012}}</ref> After two seasons with the {{UCI team code|CJR|2011}} team, [[Oleg Chuzhda]] joined the squad,<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.biciciclismo.com/cas/site/noticias-ficha.asp?id=46704|language=Spanish|title=Oleg Chuzhda disputará las Ardenas: "Este cambio es algo que necesitaba en mi carrera deportiva"|date=18 January 2012|access-date=29 March 2012|work=Biciciclismo|publisher=Gurenet Teknologia S.L.|trans-title=Oleg Chuzhda will take part in the Ardennes: "This change is something I needed in my career"}}</ref> while [[Kevyn Ista]] left {{UCI team code|COF|2011}} after two seasons,<ref name="Ista"/> with a best result of second place at the 2011 [[Le Samyn]]. The final arrival at the team for 2012 was ex-{{UCI team code|KAT|2011}} rider and three-time Belgian national time trial champion [[Leif Hoste]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cyclingnews.com/news/hoste-joins-accent-jobs-willems-verandas-for-2012|title=Hoste joins Accent Jobs-Willems Veranda's for 2012|work=Cycling News|publisher=Future Publishing Limited|date=29 November 2011|access-date=29 March 2012}}</ref> Hoste was signed to boost the team's abilities in the [[Classic cycle races|Classic races]], having been a three-time runner-up in the [[Tour of Flanders (men's race)|Tour of Flanders]] Monument race. This left the team's roster at 18 riders for the 2012 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://62.50.72.82/ucinet/default.asp?page=UCITeamsdetail&discipline=ROA&continent=ALL&teamscategory=&teamstype=PCT&year=2012&teamnameid=3341&npage=&search=&l=ENG|title=Accent Jobs-Willems Veranda's (ACC) - BEL|access-date=29 March 2012|work=[[UCI Continental Circuits]]|publisher=[[Union Cycliste Internationale]]|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304130409/http://62.50.72.82/ucinet/default.asp?page=UCITeamsdetail&discipline=ROA&continent=ALL&teamscategory=&teamstype=PCT&year=2012&teamnameid=3341&npage=&search=&l=ENG|archive-date=4 March 2016|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>

